Cost


They say  
suffering earns heaven.  
Pain is just  
the price  
of peace.  

But for me  
a bird’s call,  
the rustle of leaves,  
the breath of waves  
is more than enough.  

The little things  
are my shelter.  
Paradise feels sparse,  
sorrow inadequate  
as currency for grace.
